    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Prenatal Nutrition</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brent Kramer letter on Aug 29 article suggests feeding nursing mothers in India adequately so that their babies can thrive on breast milk alone</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Researchers Raise Fresh Issues in Breast-Feeding Debate,'' (Aug. 29) reports the dilemma faced by malnourished mothers in  India whose breast milk may not provide enough nutrition, while : recommended supplements may be dangerous in themselves. Perhaps the solution is as politically charged as it is simple: feed mothers adequately, and their babies will thrive on breast milk alone.  BRENT KRAMER  Brooklyn</p>
      </block>
